1) O-ETB Organization 

The following tools comprise the MedSecurance O-ETB assurance toolbox:
Assurance Tool - allows interactive use by users, certifiers, and developers
Assurance Server - enables programmatic invocation of background assurance services
CAP Renderer - renders assurance artifacts to satisfy specific certification requirements
Tool Agents - provide a framework and capability to incorporate external tools in the process

The tools create and use the following data collections:
Knowledge Base - organized by System Models, Argument Patterns, Workflows and General Knowledge
Assurance Case Repository - organized by assurance case identifiers
Evidence Repository - organized by class of evidence and shared among assurance cases
Certification Assurance Package (CAP) - organized by certification application

The O-ETB directory contains several subdirectories, listed below, containing source code,
repository, knowledge base, build and test facilities, and generated Certification
Assurance Packages (CAPs). Among these are directories and files associated with the
above listed tools (as indicated within parentheses).

BUILD - build/deploy the executable tools
CAP - Certification Assurance Package (CAP Renderer)
docs - design, developer, and user documentation
KB - knowledge base (Assurance Tool, Assurance Server, CAP Renderer)
	system models 
	assurance case patterns 
	workflow programs (to be used with future workflow processing extensions)
	/ MODELS / <version> / policy.pl, platform.pl, configuration.pl, ...
                             / properties / p1.pro ...
	/ PATTERNS / patterns_ISO_81001.pl, patterns_MILS.pl
	/ WORKFLOWS /
REPOSITORY - generated files for assurance CASES and EVIDENCE
	assurance case repository - (O-ETB Assurance Tool and O-ETB Assurance Server)
	evidence repository - (O-ETB Assurance Tool, O-ETB Evidence Repository and Tool Agents)
	/ CASES / <case> / repository.pl (* generated *)
	/ EVIDENCE / repository.pl (* generated *)
                   / <category> / <xref> / status, aargs, ... (* generated *)
RUNTIME - temporary and persistent auxiliary runtime files
src - source code, including subdirectories
	agent.pl
	agents (dir) - (Tool Agents)
	assurance.pl
	com (dir) - common and configuration files
		command.pl, param.pl, procs.pl, test.pl, ui.pl
	command_etb.pl, demo.pl. etb_server.pl, etb.pl, evidence.pl, export.pl, instantiate.pl,
	kb.pl, makefile, patterns.pl, procs_etb.pl, stringutil.pl
	models_api - internal APIs to access models in the KB
	/ models_api / common.pl, configuration.pl, model.pl, platform.pl, policy.pl
	...
TEST - test scripts and test cases


